Owner.Description: Enter Team or Individual Name Responsible for the Stack.

DeleteAfter.Description: Enter Date (MM/DD/YYYY). It's Ok to Delete the Stack or 'Never' if meant to be persistent.

AvailabilityZone1.Description: Enter Availability Zone 1 for Public and Private Subnets to use.

AvailabilityZone2.Description: Enter Availability Zone 2 for Public and Private Subnets to use.

RemoteAccessNetwork.Description: Source Network IP CIDR Block such as an Office that can access instances say over VPN. (i.e. 192.168.100.0/24)
RemoteAccessNetwork.ConstraintDescription: must be a valid CIDR range of the form x.x.x.x/x.

AllowHttpToPublicRuleNumber.Description: Enter Public Network ACL Rule Number to Allow HTTP From Internet to Public Network.

AllowHttpsToPublicRuleNumber.Description: Enter Public Network ACL Rule Number to Allow HTTPS From Internet to Public Network.

AllowReturnTrafficToPublicRuleNumber.Description: Enter Public Network ACL Rule Number to Allow Return Traffic From Internet to Public Network.

AllowVpcSubnetsRuleNumber.Description: Enter Public Network ACL Rule Number to Allow All VPC Subnets Cross Access to Public Network.

AllowAllOutboundPublicRuleNumber.Description: Enter Public Network ACL Rule Number to Allow All Outbound Traffic from the Public Network.

AllowAllInboundPrivateRuleNumber.Description: Enter Private Network ACL Rule Number to Allow All Inbound Traffic.

AllowAllOutboundPrivateRuleNumber.Description: Enter Private Network ACL Rule Number to Allow All Outbound Traffic.

Properties.GroupDescription: Instance to Instance Access in VPC

Owner.Description: Team or Individual that Owns this Formation.

PublicRouteTable.Description: Public Route Table Created for VPC

PrivateRouteTable.Description: Private Route Table Created for VPC

PublicNetworkAcl.Description: Public Network ACL Created for VPC

PrivateNetworkAcl.Description: Private Netowrk ACL Created for VPC

AvailabilityZone1.Description: Private Subnet IDs Created for VPC

AvailabilityZone2.Description: Private Subnet IDs Created for VPC

PublicSubnetCidr1.Description: Public Subnet IDs Created for VPC

PublicSubnetCidr2.Description: Public Subnet IDs Created for VPC

PrivateSubnetCidr1.Description: Private Subnet IDs Created for VPC

PrivateSubnetCidr2.Description: Private Subnet IDs Created for VPC

InternalAccessSecurityGroup.Description: Instance to Instance Access within VPC

RemoteAccessSecurityGroup.Description: Remote Network or IP that can Access the instances of VPN or Direct Connect.

PublicNetworkACLRuleNumbers.Description: Public Network ACL Rules Numbers Created.

PrivateNetworkACLRuleNumbers.Description: Private Network ACL Rules Numbers Created.

DeleteAfter.Description: It is ok to delete this Formation after this date
